@page
@model dynamic
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Engine";
}
<section class="page-header">
    <h1>The COR0110268.11P Governance Engine</h1>
    <p>A configurable core that turns governance principles into executable logic.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>From Principles to Execution</h2>
    <p>The engine ingests governance inputs—policies, standards, regulations, and organizational rules—and transforms them into structured components: policies, workflows, decision paths, and enforcement rules.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Key Engine Layers</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-grid">
        <li><strong>Policy Layer:</strong> Encodes rules, constraints, and obligations.</li>
        <li><strong>Decision Layer:</strong> Manages approvals, escalations, and decision trees.</li>
        <li><strong>Workflow Layer:</strong> Orchestrates processes and ensures they follow governance paths.</li>
        <li><strong>Observation Layer:</strong> Monitors events, actions, and signals for compliance.</li>
        <li><strong>Audit Layer:</strong> Records every decision and rule evaluation for traceability.</li>
        <li><strong>Integration Layer:</strong> Connects the engine to external systems, data, and interfaces.</li>
    </ul>
</section>
